## BioGate x Dorm Room Fund – Deck Outline

Target: 8–10 slides, 10-minute conversation, optimized for DRF partners.

---

### Slide 1 – Title

- **Title:** BioGate
- **Subtitle:** AI vendor risk platform for biotech & life-science supply chains
- Founder name(s), school(s)
- Contact: email / site

---

### Slide 2 – Founder Story / Why This

- Who you are (student, background).
- How you ran into or discovered the BIOSECURE / sanctions vendor problem.
- 1–2 bullets that show you “go unreasonably deep” (e.g., built BIS ingestion scripts, read the BIOSECURE text, talked to X compliance folks).

---

### Slide 3 – Problem

- Biotech / life-science vendor compliance is:
  - Manual spreadsheets + government websites.
  - Slow, error-prone.
  - Getting harder due to BIOSECURE / BIS / OFAC / UFLPA.
- Concrete example:
  - “Compliance weeks of work to clear one vendor list.”

---

### Slide 4 – Solution

- Diagram: CSV of vendors → BioGate → audit API + dashboard.
- Callouts:
  - Ingests BIS/OFAC/UFLPA.
  - Fuzzy matching + Claude normalization + parent expansion.
  - Risk tiers + evidence for legal/compliance sign-off.

---

### Slide 5 – How It Works (Under the Hood)

- Supabase watchlist ingestion (BIS, pattern for OFAC/UFLPA).
- Fuzzy matching with Rapidfuzz (names + aliases).
- Claude API:
  - normalized_name
  - country_hint
  - parent_company_hint
  - equipment_type_hint
- Risk model: Red/Amber/Yellow/Green with parent-company overrides.

Keep this high-level; don’t do a live demo.

---

### Slide 6 – Traction (Week 3)

- Supabase live; BIS ingestion script in production.
- `/audits/upload` FastAPI endpoint completed.
- Audit + vendor tables with risk tiers and evidence.
- Integration tests:
  - 10-vendor CSV fixture.
  - Correctly flags BGI / Huawei as high-risk.
  - Non-red expectations for others (with one xfail around Agilent).
- Early convos with [X] labs / biotechs (add specifics).

---

### Slide 7 – Market & Wedge

- Initial customers: US biotech / CRO / labs with:
  - >X vendors.
  - Regulatory exposure (BIOSECURE, export control).
- TAM narrative:
  - Compliance & risk budget in life sciences.
  - Adjacent expansion (medtech, deep-tech hardware).

---

### Slide 8 – Business Model & GTM

- SaaS pricing:
  - By number of vendor audits / vendor count / spend.
- GTM:
  - Start with 1–3 paid pilots (design partners).
  - Expand within org (multi-teams, multi-sites).
  - Eventually: integrations with popular ERPs/procurement tools.

---

### Slide 9 – Roadmap (Next 6–12 Months)

- Near term:
  - OFAC/UFLPA ingestion.
  - Composite risk scoring engine.
  - First design partners live.
- Medium term:
  - Deeper integrations.
  - Broader watchlist coverage.
  - First $Xk MRR.

---

### Slide 10 – Why DRF / The Ask

- Why you want DRF:
  - Student-focused capital.
  - Network of early-stage SaaS and infra founders.
  - Help with design partners and next round.
- The ask:
  - $90k–$250k on DRF standard terms.
  - Specific intros (biotech / compliance leaders, etc.).

